article.description: Rodell Wigginton scored 25 points off the bench, leading six players in double digits, as Buffalo rolled over Division III Pittsburgh-Bradford 109-49 on Friday night.
article.headline: Buffalo rolls over Div. III Pitt-Bradford 109-49
article.linkText: Buffalo rolls over Div. III Pitt-Bradford 109-49
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Rodell Wigginton scored 25 points off the bench, leading six players in double digits, as Buffalo rolled over Division III Pittsburgh-Bradford 109-49 on Friday night. Wigginton hit 10 of 12 from the field and 4 of 4 from the line for the Bulls. He also led the team with 10 rebounds. Blake Hamilton scored 21 points, C.J. Massinburg had 19 points, Lamonte Bearden had 13, Nick Perkins had 12 and Willie Conner 10. Buffalo outrebounded the Panthers 49-34 and forced 25 turnovers. Buffalo scored 26 straight points to start the first half and led 59-14 at the break. Wigginton slammed a pair of dunks early in the second half and Hamilton and Bearden sank back-to-back 3-pointers midway for an 81-27 advantage and the Bulls never looked back. Evan Greening scored 20 points and grabbed 14 boards for the Panthers.
